1
00:00:01,134 --> 00:00:06,542
(This murderer imitates the murders
in an underground manga called Nekros.)

2
00:00:09,411 --> 00:00:10,970
This is the work of a serial killer?

3
00:00:11,470 --> 00:00:13,306
I’m sure it is.

4
00:00:14,179 --> 00:00:15,697
His pen name is Mr. Kill.

5
00:00:17,060 --> 00:00:18,817
I bet some editors have seen
his work before.

6
00:00:18,962 --> 00:00:20,139
Oh, Mr. Kaye.

7
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:23,140
Inspector, the editor’s in today.

8
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,657
We’re looking for the artist
behind this manga.

9
00:01:24,441 --> 00:01:25,779
Where are you rushing off to, Mr. Kaye?

10
00:01:39,509 --> 00:01:40,619
Anti-anxiety med…

11
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,903
You look distressed.

12
00:02:02,863 --> 00:02:03,856
Take it easy.

13
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:08,780
We…

14
00:02:10,608 --> 00:02:12,337
We have a lot to talk about.

15
00:03:45,057 --> 00:03:45,656
Hey.

16
00:03:47,524 --> 00:03:48,139
Yes?

17
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,857
Do you recognize this art style?

18
00:04:21,475 --> 00:04:23,177
Uhh, no, no, I don’t.

19
00:04:24,703 --> 00:04:25,942
I’ve never seen this before.

20
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:29,340
And if you actually think about it,
a work of this violet nature,

21
00:04:29,382 --> 00:04:31,377
compared to mine,

22
00:04:32,044 --> 00:04:33,980
is completely opposite.

23
00:04:34,768 --> 00:04:36,260
Like, look.

24
00:04:37,776 --> 00:04:39,602
I do think it looks familiar.

25
00:04:40,198 --> 00:04:42,617
It looks like an old art style of…

26
00:04:44,257 --> 00:04:47,297
If I ever drew something
as graphic as this,

27
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:49,545
I’d probably lose all my fans.

28
00:04:50,777 --> 00:04:51,579
Inspector.

29
00:04:53,134 --> 00:04:55,219
The editor said this art style

30
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:57,650
looks like it belongs to an artist
named Kaye.

31
00:05:01,992 --> 00:05:04,979
I–I think he must have misunderstood.

32
00:05:05,605 --> 00:05:07,379
Oh, he’s right.

33
00:05:07,788 --> 00:05:10,259
Kaye hasn’t written anything experimental
like this for a long time.

34
00:05:10,371 --> 00:05:11,900
This won’t sell.

35
00:05:12,336 --> 00:05:14,100
I might really have misunderstood.

36
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,700
Many artists draw like that
these days, you know?

37
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,540
Follow him.

38
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:17,142
Have your fill.

39
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,459
Because I…

40
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:23,500
might not be able to come
and feed you anymore.

41
00:06:34,588 --> 00:06:35,262
Inspector.

42
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:37,900
Why are you suspecting him?

43
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,982
People don’t panic like that

44
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:45,817
even when being cornered.

45
00:06:46,779 --> 00:06:48,897
Only someone with a secret does.

46
00:06:50,405 --> 00:06:53,299
When he feels safe and at ease,

47
00:06:53,736 --> 00:06:54,896
this is how he is.

48
00:06:56,299 --> 00:06:59,902
Let’s see if he’s gonna stay that way.

49
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:01,616
I have to go.

50
00:07:36,072 --> 00:07:37,900
I’ve got Kaye’s previous works.

51
00:07:38,626 --> 00:07:41,860
The publishing house’s database
is full of artwork like this.

52
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,657
What do you want to do now?

53
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,220
Looks like he’s going outside.

54
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:19,770
METROPOLITAN INVESTIGATIVE BUREAU

55
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,100
Are you sure about this?

56
00:08:30,590 --> 00:08:32,062
We don’t have a warrant, sir.

57
00:08:32,730 --> 00:08:33,770
We could get sued for this.

58
00:08:33,982 --> 00:08:35,420
Not if he never finds out.

59
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:37,059
We’ll just get in

60
00:08:37,739 --> 00:08:38,657
and get out.

61
00:08:40,936 --> 00:08:41,583
Yes, sir.

62
00:09:08,422 --> 00:09:09,262
Whoa.

63
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:12,102
This is K.Cupid’s room?

64
00:09:14,048 --> 00:09:15,460
It’s kinda spooky, sir.

65
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,539
I’m installing a remote software.

66
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:39,302
It can restore any recently deleted files.

67
00:09:55,157 --> 00:09:55,859
Okay.

68
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:04,659
A photo with a fan, huh?

69
00:10:05,693 --> 00:10:06,342
Wait.

70
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,616
Isn’t that you, Inspector?

71
00:10:13,225 --> 00:10:14,265
Oh!

72
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,537
Mr. Kaye!

73
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,739
He’s the guy whose autograph
was on your jacket that day!

74
00:10:19,117 --> 00:10:20,300
Oh, Inspector.

75
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:22,259
Why didn’t you tell me
you’re into that kind of manga?

76
00:10:22,275 --> 00:10:24,259
Who’d have thought
from your usual smolder?

77
00:10:24,303 --> 00:10:25,180
We’re working.

78
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:26,998
Get it done and over with.

79
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:28,500
Yes, sir.

80
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:33,460
(Sir, the target is on his way to you.)

81
00:12:12,841 --> 00:12:13,579
Yes?

82
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,060
I’m on my way.

83
00:12:16,656 --> 00:12:17,300
Of course.

84
00:12:37,294 --> 00:12:38,177
I’m off, Mom.

85
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:38,936
Prim.

86
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:40,902
Don’t forget to drink this.

87
00:12:41,299 --> 00:12:42,220
You’re the best.

88
00:12:44,002 --> 00:12:45,100
Oh, Praew.

89
00:12:46,019 --> 00:12:47,220
You’re early.

90
00:12:48,337 --> 00:12:49,297
You had breakfast?

91
00:12:49,574 --> 00:12:51,017
No, I didn’t.

92
00:12:58,389 --> 00:12:58,940
Here.

93
00:12:58,962 --> 00:13:00,017
To start off your day.

94
00:13:04,577 --> 00:13:05,499
Is it good?

95
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:06,537
Thank you.

96
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,023
Shall we?

97
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:17,779
Hello.

98
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:41,057
What should we do?

99
00:13:41,277 --> 00:13:43,540
Yesterday Thun didn’t tell us
what we had to do at all.

100
00:13:44,103 --> 00:13:45,703
Should we ask these people

101
00:13:45,977 --> 00:13:47,185
if they need us for anything?

102
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,940
Hey, guys. Welcome to your first day.

103
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:51,797
Here.

104
00:13:52,931 --> 00:13:55,182
This is all the information
on the two murders.

105
00:13:55,465 --> 00:13:58,740
Try to analyze it and compare it
to the manga shot by shot.

106
00:13:59,062 --> 00:14:02,622
Find a connection
that this is no coincidence.

107
00:14:03,594 --> 00:14:04,499
Can you do that?

108
00:14:04,954 --> 00:14:05,813
Of course.

109
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:07,862
Yes, of course.

110
00:14:08,408 --> 00:14:09,179
Okay.

111
00:14:09,617 --> 00:14:12,210
I don’t care whether you’re young or old.

112
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:13,897
I only care that you’re hard working.

113
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:15,702
Give it a shot.

114
00:14:20,494 --> 00:14:21,097
Alright.

115
00:14:21,180 --> 00:14:22,019
Let’s begin.

116
00:14:24,016 --> 00:14:25,736
Oh, wow, we might as well die.

117
00:14:25,980 --> 00:14:29,457
I bet it will take us a whole week
to read through all this.

118
00:14:30,034 --> 00:14:31,342
And it’s just the two of us?

119
00:14:31,783 --> 00:14:33,062
Come on.

120
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,342
It’s good that we get to do
real work, right?

121
00:14:35,736 --> 00:14:37,694
I’d say it’s better than
taking coffee orders.

122
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:40,453
Alright. I’ll do my best.

123
00:14:41,573 --> 00:14:42,300
Alright!

124
00:14:42,811 --> 00:14:43,774
Let’s get to work.

125
00:14:44,179 --> 00:14:44,980
Slay.

126
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,330
Look at this.

127
00:14:57,740 --> 00:15:00,699
The rope and the wounds
are exactly the same.

128
00:15:00,871 --> 00:15:02,499
This can't be a coincidence.

129
00:15:02,777 --> 00:15:05,576
I think the murderer didn’t just kill
to imitate the manga,

130
00:15:06,085 --> 00:15:09,460
I think they even made sure
the setup looks exactly alike.

131
00:15:10,878 --> 00:15:11,817
Honestly…

132
00:15:12,158 --> 00:15:15,696
I didn’t think you’d be a fan
of such a graphic manga, Praew.

133
00:15:16,637 --> 00:15:19,016
I guess I’m kinda repressed.

134
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:23,142
I don’t have any power in real life,
so I find comfort in manga like this.

135
00:15:23,470 --> 00:15:24,340
It’s cathartic.

136
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,497
I understand.

137
00:15:27,746 --> 00:15:30,530
Oh, I’ve read through
the details of both cases.

138
00:15:30,774 --> 00:15:31,979
Shall we combine it?

139
00:15:32,478 --> 00:15:36,983
I’m dying to see Thun so stunned
his jaw drops to the floor.

140
00:15:37,180 --> 00:15:37,934
That’s good.

141
00:15:39,576 --> 00:15:41,063
So this page…

142
00:15:41,222 --> 00:15:42,222
And this one…

143
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:19,816
Inspector.

144
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:21,980
Isn’t this cat food?

145
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:23,543
Yeah.

146
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,619
Did you grab the wrong bag or what?

147
00:16:26,626 --> 00:16:27,423
No.

148
00:16:32,022 --> 00:16:33,459
Ugh, it’s so fishy!

149
00:16:42,974 --> 00:16:43,857
Hello.

150
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:45,820
You’re lucky today, huh?

151
00:16:46,035 --> 00:16:47,503
Someone already fed you.

152
00:16:57,934 --> 00:16:58,782
I have to go.

153
00:16:59,088 --> 00:17:00,020
See you later.

154
00:17:29,914 --> 00:17:30,659
Yes?

155
00:17:33,466 --> 00:17:34,020
Oh.

156
00:17:34,308 --> 00:17:35,097
Of course.

157
00:17:38,777 --> 00:17:39,499
Inspector.

158
00:17:40,670 --> 00:17:42,604
IT just told me
they found something important.

159
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:54,900
IT looked through Kaye’s IP address

160
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:59,056
and found that he’s accessed Nekros blog’s
back-end system several times.

161
00:18:04,002 --> 00:18:05,137
More importantly,

162
00:18:06,017 --> 00:18:09,200
they’re able to recover more than 50%
of the files deleted.

163
00:18:13,185 --> 00:18:15,100
It’s Nekros’ manuscript.

164
00:18:21,645 --> 00:18:25,140
Inspector, only the artist himself
would have something like that.

165
00:18:27,826 --> 00:18:29,293
I think Kaye is Mr. Kill.

166
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,059
Proceed with the team.

167
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:35,503
Issue an arrest warrant.

168
00:18:36,108 --> 00:18:36,817
Yes.

169
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:39,897
We’re bringing him into custody.

170
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:37,423
What happened?

171
00:19:37,623 --> 00:19:38,736
Don’t tell me he got away.

172
00:19:38,826 --> 00:19:39,417
Yes, sir.

173
00:19:39,699 --> 00:19:41,290
I bet he’s still around here somewhere.

174
00:19:41,468 --> 00:19:42,337
Spread out.

175
00:19:42,577 --> 00:19:44,254
Be careful. He could be armed.

176
00:19:44,419 --> 00:19:45,137
Yes, sir.

177
00:19:46,253 --> 00:19:46,863
Let’s go.

178
00:19:49,964 --> 00:19:50,940
Bun, Nat, go that way.

179
00:19:51,017 --> 00:19:51,702
Yes, sir.

180
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:58,194
Nop, you go there.

181
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:58,893
Yes, sir.

182
00:20:10,148 --> 00:20:12,699
I’m–I’m sorry.

183
00:20:12,736 --> 00:20:13,709
I won’t run anymore.

184
00:20:13,734 --> 00:20:16,339
But I really don’t have it.

185
00:20:17,210 --> 00:20:19,179
You gave Chid all the money yesterday,
didn’t you?

186
00:20:19,448 --> 00:20:21,496
They told me you’re here.

187
00:20:22,939 --> 00:20:23,736
Where’s my money?

188
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:27,887
I gave them all the money.

189
00:20:27,906 --> 00:20:29,385
I don’t have anything right now.

190
00:20:29,893 --> 00:20:31,979
Will you try to understand me a little?

191
00:20:32,977 --> 00:20:34,176
No, I won’t!

192
00:20:36,017 --> 00:20:37,100
It’s my money.

193
00:20:37,739 --> 00:20:39,543
You will give it back to me.

194
00:20:40,694 --> 00:20:41,540
Turn out his bag.

195
00:20:51,540 --> 00:20:53,020
Oh, he has a hammer.

196
00:20:56,259 --> 00:20:57,454
Why are you carrying a hammer?

197
00:20:58,460 --> 00:20:59,783
Are you gonna smash our heads open?

198
00:21:00,139 --> 00:21:00,782
Huh?

199
00:21:02,586 --> 00:21:05,023
You think this is Whac-A-Mole
or something?

200
00:21:05,817 --> 00:21:06,977
You’re broke, huh?

201
00:21:07,471 --> 00:21:08,265
That’s fine.

202
00:21:09,586 --> 00:21:12,240
I’ll just take what little interest
you can pay up for now.

203
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:24,945
Hammer, huh?

204
00:21:25,275 --> 00:21:26,200
How arrogant!

205
00:21:26,222 --> 00:21:27,051
How dare you!

206
00:21:27,260 --> 00:21:28,463
You dare bring a hammer!

207
00:21:28,505 --> 00:21:30,500
You planned to hurt us? Huh?

208
00:21:34,425 --> 00:21:36,620
Your father may be gone,

209
00:21:37,444 --> 00:21:38,730
but his debt isn’t.

210
00:21:39,825 --> 00:21:41,260
You gotta pay for it.

211
00:21:42,177 --> 00:21:43,540
If you don’t,

212
00:21:44,380 --> 00:21:46,460
just be ready to meet your dad
in the grave.

213
00:21:50,573 --> 00:21:51,262
Let’s go.

214
00:22:48,694 --> 00:22:49,620
You sure you good?

215
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:50,739
I don’t have a connection, man.

216
00:22:50,755 --> 00:22:52,054
I’m out of data.

217
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,300
Just hurry up.

218
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,100
Drop your weapon.

219
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:44,299
I said drop your weapon!

220
00:24:49,217 --> 00:24:50,380
Hey! Drop your weapon!

221
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:00,300
Slowly.

222
00:26:05,450 --> 00:26:07,179
The doctor said you’ll be fine.

223
00:26:08,620 --> 00:26:10,903
It’s just some scratches
and a cut on your head.

224
00:26:13,786 --> 00:26:14,619
Speaking of which…

225
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:17,777
What should I call you?

226
00:26:20,583 --> 00:26:21,616
Atima?

227
00:26:23,820 --> 00:26:25,017
Chankacha?

228
00:26:30,170 --> 00:26:31,379
K.Cupid?

229
00:26:36,173 --> 00:26:37,257
Or Mr. Kill?

230
00:26:47,426 --> 00:26:49,143
Your name changes history…

231
00:26:50,737 --> 00:26:53,419
Five times in five years.

232
00:26:57,539 --> 00:27:00,180
The IP address used to log into
the back-end system of Nekros blog…

233
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,862
is at your place.

234
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:04,740
Am I right?

235
00:27:09,311 --> 00:27:10,099
Oh…

236
00:27:10,955 --> 00:27:14,899
There’s also the high definition
manuscript you deleted.

237
00:27:20,062 --> 00:27:21,345
What I said just now…

238
00:27:22,740 --> 00:27:24,140
Was any of it incorrect?

239
00:27:37,527 --> 00:27:38,216
Hey.

240
00:27:40,023 --> 00:27:42,777
Silence won’t save you, Mr. Kaye.

241
00:27:48,337 --> 00:27:49,459
Right now,

242
00:27:56,270 --> 00:27:59,380
you’re the prime suspect
in the serial murder case.

243
00:28:05,706 --> 00:28:07,859
Do you understand your situation?

244
00:28:19,245 --> 00:28:20,659
Well, then, let me ask…

245
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:24,256
Last night,

246
00:28:25,420 --> 00:28:27,099
what were you doing in a dark alley?

247
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,979
Why did you run when you saw the police?

248
00:28:35,768 --> 00:28:37,497
I–I…

249
00:28:38,540 --> 00:28:39,497
I didn’t do it.

250
00:28:39,823 --> 00:28:40,500
Hey!

251
00:28:41,540 --> 00:28:45,419
What innocent man walks around
with a hammer covered in blood

252
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:48,090
alone in a dark alley
in the middle of the night?

253
00:28:56,620 --> 00:28:57,617
Why do you carry it?

254
00:29:02,902 --> 00:29:04,822
For your next victim?

255
00:29:12,697 --> 00:29:14,176
It–It’s not like that.

256
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:16,017
I carry it…

257
00:29:19,102 --> 00:29:20,425
For self-defense.

258
00:29:24,521 --> 00:29:25,460
Self-defense?

259
00:29:26,934 --> 00:29:27,820
From who?

260
00:29:32,017 --> 00:29:32,780
The…

261
00:29:35,537 --> 00:29:36,739
Debt collectors.

262
00:29:55,370 --> 00:29:56,139
Okay.

263
00:29:58,622 --> 00:30:00,183
The debt collectors

264
00:30:01,441 --> 00:30:04,617
and the hammer check out.

265
00:30:10,257 --> 00:30:11,500
But explain this…

266
00:30:16,380 --> 00:30:18,937
Why are these two cases

267
00:30:23,020 --> 00:30:24,534
exactly like your manga?

268
00:30:37,638 --> 00:30:39,174
I–I don’t know.

269
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:41,542
I wrote from my imagination.

270
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:46,260
I’m telling the truth.

271
00:30:46,395 --> 00:30:47,463
I swear.

272
00:30:47,862 --> 00:30:50,457
I don’t know anything about this
and I didn’t kill anyone.

273
00:31:02,620 --> 00:31:03,380
Thank you.

274
00:31:10,190 --> 00:31:11,297
Oh, Inspector.

275
00:31:12,820 --> 00:31:14,540
This guy’s life has been one living hell.

276
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:20,500
His father was one of the suspects
in the Thai Investment Bank 20 years ago.

277
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:31,539
He was charged with fraud
and declared bankrupt.

278
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:35,102
His father is dead now.

279
00:31:35,454 --> 00:31:37,060
But he’s still paying for that debt.

280
00:31:39,659 --> 00:31:40,942
And the weapon analysis?

281
00:31:42,220 --> 00:31:43,020
Almost done.

282
00:31:48,540 --> 00:31:50,254
He’s still a suspect.

283
00:31:51,598 --> 00:31:52,579
We’re keeping him in custody.

284
00:31:52,860 --> 00:31:53,540
Yes, sir.

285
00:32:12,099 --> 00:32:14,130
(What looks like coincidences
at first glance)

286
00:32:14,429 --> 00:32:16,690
(has been proven by my team.)

287
00:32:16,985 --> 00:32:20,697
(It is undeniable that the details
left behind by the murderer)

288
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,570
(are the exact replica
of the manga Nekros.)

289
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:25,050
(There’s only one question left:)
MURDERS IMITATE MANGA

290
00:32:25,260 --> 00:32:28,622
(Will the murderer stop here
or will he do it again?)

291
00:32:30,565 --> 00:32:31,662
Listen, you guys.

292
00:32:31,983 --> 00:32:33,539
This is amazing.

293
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:36,983
The hashtag Looking For Nekros
is still in top trending today.

294
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:38,494
That’s so cool.

295
00:32:41,210 --> 00:32:44,622
You two are more than
just interns now, you know?

296
00:32:45,102 --> 00:32:47,810
You proved this is true.

297
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:49,448
Let’s give them a round of applause.

298
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,379
You don’t believe you could do it?

299
00:33:10,933 --> 00:33:11,625
I do.

300
00:33:12,131 --> 00:33:13,660
I’m just still confused.

301
00:33:14,419 --> 00:33:16,460
Let’s pack up and celebrate.

302
00:33:20,817 --> 00:33:22,065
What should we have for dinner?

303
00:33:22,710 --> 00:33:23,700
You can pick.

304
00:33:25,047 --> 00:33:26,096
Well…

305
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:27,499
Barbecue?

306
00:33:28,202 --> 00:33:29,302
Nah. My hair’d smell of smoke.

307
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:30,936
Hotpot?

308
00:33:31,300 --> 00:33:32,019
Not bad.

309
00:33:32,096 --> 00:33:32,814
Okay.

310
00:33:39,460 --> 00:33:40,700
Traikanawut.

311
00:33:41,222 --> 00:33:42,536
That’s a familiar surname.

312
00:33:47,022 --> 00:33:47,617
Oh?

313
00:33:47,782 --> 00:33:49,062
Praew, wait up.

314
00:34:07,848 --> 00:34:09,060
Everyone knows

315
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:15,019
my dad was the dirty cop
in the Thai Investment case.

316
00:34:17,337 --> 00:34:20,890
Who knows how many people
killed themselves because of him?

317
00:34:21,130 --> 00:34:22,939
But my parents are dead.

318
00:34:24,537 --> 00:34:27,779
Only my brother and I
were left to carry their sin.

319
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:34,382
Who your father was
has nothing to do with who you are.

320
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:38,179
Surnames are nothing
but a word on your badge.

321
00:34:39,090 --> 00:34:42,140
It’s what you do that defines you, Praew.

322
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:46,580
To me,

323
00:34:47,899 --> 00:34:49,976
you’re the coolest friend ever.

324
00:34:51,497 --> 00:34:53,820
Stop looking so glum!

325
00:35:13,260 --> 00:35:14,863
He’s been pacing around for hours.

326
00:35:16,650 --> 00:35:19,342
He doesn’t ask for water or food,
and he doesn’t say a word.

327
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,650
ททท

328
00:35:48,579 --> 00:35:49,222
Uh…

329
00:35:49,297 --> 00:35:50,222
Anybody there?

330
00:35:50,857 --> 00:35:52,099
Officer?

331
00:35:52,296 --> 00:35:53,256
Is anybody there?

332
00:35:53,281 --> 00:35:55,660
There’s going to be another victim!

333
00:35:56,011 --> 00:35:56,860
Officer!

334
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,240
Is anybody there?

335
00:36:04,670 --> 00:36:05,739
Officer.

336
00:36:06,291 --> 00:36:08,217
Take a look at these again.

337
00:36:12,860 --> 00:36:17,014
I don’t think the murderer imitates
my manga just to feed his own ego.

338
00:36:17,140 --> 00:36:18,776
He’s trying to communicate

339
00:36:18,962 --> 00:36:22,537
by leaving clues in the crime scenes
in a way that no one else would notice.

340
00:36:23,259 --> 00:36:24,779
Like this one.

341
00:36:25,102 --> 00:36:26,383
From the look of it,

342
00:36:26,665 --> 00:36:29,862
it’s nothing more than
the victim’s attempt at saving his life.

343
00:36:30,077 --> 00:36:30,859
But…

344
00:36:31,585 --> 00:36:33,460
What if the murderer actually
meant to leave a clue

345
00:36:33,478 --> 00:36:34,930
meaning the number 10?

346
00:36:36,071 --> 00:36:38,260
And what does ‘10’ mean?

347
00:36:39,180 --> 00:36:43,217
It means the next victim
comes from Chapter 10 of Nekros.

348
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,902
And that became this case.

349
00:36:48,394 --> 00:36:49,296
Nonsense.

350
00:36:50,330 --> 00:36:52,054
Blood splattered everywhere.

351
00:36:52,659 --> 00:36:56,219
The victim was hit in the head
and bloodily struggling on the floor.

352
00:36:56,835 --> 00:36:58,450
It was only natural all 10
of his fingerprints were on the floor.

353
00:36:59,942 --> 00:37:00,743
Inspector.

354
00:37:01,337 --> 00:37:02,980
I think it’s just a coincidence.

355
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:04,580
He’s just making things up.

356
00:37:12,816 --> 00:37:14,417
If your theory is right,

357
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:17,176
what about the second case?

358
00:37:18,140 --> 00:37:19,496
In the permanent secretary case,

359
00:37:20,986 --> 00:37:22,170
what clue did the murderer leave?

360
00:37:26,317 --> 00:37:28,540
The permanent secretary case

361
00:37:29,139 --> 00:37:31,696
happened in Chapter 10 of Nekros.

362
00:37:31,939 --> 00:37:35,777
But I wrote this panel as the cover
for Chapter 14 of Nekros.

363
00:37:36,330 --> 00:37:39,620
In my opinion, I think the murderer
is giving us a clue that

364
00:37:40,148 --> 00:37:42,902
the next victim is going to
come from Nekros,

365
00:37:44,016 --> 00:37:45,142
Chapter 14.

366
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:02,336
Is Chapter 14 in the files we recovered?

367
00:38:03,379 --> 00:38:05,302
Some files were destroyed in the process,

368
00:38:05,706 --> 00:38:07,185
and I couldn’t recover all of it.

369
00:38:07,571 --> 00:38:08,782
I’m not sure, sir.

370
00:38:09,266 --> 00:38:10,139
Look it up.

371
00:38:13,857 --> 00:38:15,019
I found it, sir.

372
00:38:15,180 --> 00:38:16,097
It’s intact.

373
00:38:16,456 --> 00:38:17,379
Open it.

374
00:38:29,186 --> 00:38:29,859
Uh…

375
00:38:31,034 --> 00:38:35,462
Chapter 14 of Nekros
is about a famous lawyer

376
00:38:36,425 --> 00:38:39,703
who uses his words
and the loophole in the laws

377
00:38:40,136 --> 00:38:44,583
to frame scapegoats
in order to save his rich clients

378
00:38:44,736 --> 00:38:45,900
from going to jail.

379
00:38:46,798 --> 00:38:47,900
In the end,

380
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:51,737
the murderer, Nekros, kills this lawyer,

381
00:38:52,362 --> 00:38:54,463
and sews his mouth shut

382
00:38:55,220 --> 00:38:58,983
as a symbol that he will never tell
another lie again.

383
00:39:03,090 --> 00:39:05,780
I think the next victim is going to be…

384
00:39:06,850 --> 00:39:08,696
a rule-bending defense attorney.

385
00:39:14,830 --> 00:39:16,219
The first two victims

386
00:39:16,740 --> 00:39:18,370
were a civil servant and a businessman.

387
00:39:18,970 --> 00:39:20,577
Which coincide
with both chapters of Nekros.

388
00:39:21,340 --> 00:39:22,745
His theory might be right.

389
00:39:23,002 --> 00:39:25,380
How many evil lawyers do you think
there are in this country?

390
00:39:27,979 --> 00:39:29,502
How will we know who’s the target?

391
00:39:32,410 --> 00:39:35,780
This murderer is meticulous
with their plans.

392
00:39:36,190 --> 00:39:37,497
According to the first two cases,

393
00:39:38,180 --> 00:39:39,788
the victims were locked up for three days

394
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:41,136
before they got killed.

395
00:39:41,635 --> 00:39:45,620
So what the murderer needs is time.

396
00:39:46,700 --> 00:39:52,019
They need time to find the right place
and time to set up to imitate Nekros.

397
00:39:55,899 --> 00:39:57,336
Look through our nation-wide database.

398
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,417
We’re looking for a lawyer
who’s been reported missing,

399
00:40:00,651 --> 00:40:02,770
or been incommunicado
for the last few days.

400
00:40:03,210 --> 00:40:05,896
If we find someone like that,
by all means assume that

401
00:40:06,217 --> 00:40:08,739
this is the next victim of Nekros.

402
00:40:08,976 --> 00:40:09,662
Yes, sir.

403
00:40:22,510 --> 00:40:23,259
Inspector.

404
00:40:24,863 --> 00:40:28,420
We got five more reports
for missing lawyers with ambiguous history.

405
00:40:55,349 --> 00:40:56,063
Here.

406
00:40:59,808 --> 00:41:00,783
I’m not hungry.

407
00:41:03,140 --> 00:41:06,822
I can’t have you saying us police officers
don’t take good care of our suspects.

408
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:09,377
It’s not like I’m allowed to say anything.

409
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:16,379
Just eat.

410
00:41:17,410 --> 00:41:18,942
I didn’t put anything weird in there,

411
00:41:21,019 --> 00:41:22,296
except my well wishes.

412
00:41:25,339 --> 00:41:26,616
I can’t stomach anything.

413
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:34,980
Stubborn bastard.

414
00:41:40,253 --> 00:41:41,140
Give me your hands.

415
00:41:47,854 --> 00:41:50,019
Can I go home now?

416
00:41:51,820 --> 00:41:52,502
No.

417
00:41:55,016 --> 00:41:55,699
What?

418
00:41:57,974 --> 00:42:01,020
You must stay where I can see you 24/7.

419
00:42:02,300 --> 00:42:04,177
At least until we find that lawyer.

420
00:42:05,731 --> 00:42:08,130
We have to be sure
you’re not just messing with us.

421
00:42:09,028 --> 00:42:09,939
You go where I go.

422
00:42:10,217 --> 00:42:11,137
Eat where I eat.

423
00:42:11,417 --> 00:42:12,340
Sleep where I sleep.

424
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:17,416
And if I need to go to the toilet?

425
00:42:17,982 --> 00:42:18,857
I’ll go with you.

426
00:42:19,754 --> 00:42:20,786
Are you for real?

427
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:25,096
Oh.

428
00:42:26,380 --> 00:42:27,779
And don’t even think about running.

429
00:42:28,619 --> 00:42:29,819
If you do,

430
00:42:30,570 --> 00:42:32,499
I’m not above shooting you in the leg.

431
00:42:36,703 --> 00:42:37,494
Got it?

432
00:42:42,579 --> 00:42:43,416
Yes.

433
00:43:15,164 --> 00:43:18,020
How are you gonna hammer
someone’s head in that state?

434
00:43:50,817 --> 00:43:52,340
Three of these, please.

435
00:43:53,740 --> 00:43:55,019
Three bags…

436
00:43:55,540 --> 00:43:57,136
That makes 210 baht.

437
00:44:09,019 --> 00:44:11,180
Can I have one instead?

438
00:44:11,340 --> 00:44:12,731
I’ll return the rest.

439
00:44:12,755 --> 00:44:13,737
Of course.

440
00:44:14,019 --> 00:44:15,376
That’s 70 baht.

441
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:20,660
-Here.
-Thank you.

442
00:44:21,228 --> 00:44:21,866
Thank you.

443
00:44:21,891 --> 00:44:22,700
Of course.

444
00:44:52,228 --> 00:44:52,903
Uh…

445
00:44:53,583 --> 00:44:55,702
I’ll take these two he didn’t get.

446
00:44:56,500 --> 00:44:57,306
Of course.

447
00:44:57,997 --> 00:45:00,100
Two bags. That’s 140 baht.

448
00:45:01,456 --> 00:45:02,179
Okay.

449
00:45:05,376 --> 00:45:05,893
Here.

450
00:45:05,912 --> 00:45:06,940
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

451
00:45:17,465 --> 00:45:21,500
You think I’m okay with my manga
being used as death sentences?

452
00:45:26,481 --> 00:45:29,977
From now on, you’re not a suspect.

453
00:45:30,551 --> 00:45:31,810
Sorry I’m late.

454
00:45:32,029 --> 00:45:35,939
You’re the special consultant
to the Nekros Investigative Team.

455
00:45:38,420 --> 00:45:40,617
If you want to stop feeling
so guilty about it,

456
00:45:40,650 --> 00:45:41,530
work with me.

457
00:45:43,050 --> 00:45:44,016
Let’s catch this guy.

